{"type":"text","timestamp":1773433294554,"sessionID":"ses_31723c2d1ffefQggw4LJSMu73r","part":{"id":"prt_ce8dc7cab001btCWDXVS4AJXEM","sessionID":"ses_31723c2d1ffefQggw4LJSMu73r","messageID":"msg_ce8dc7217001bjBvWpChxREEGL","type":"text","text":"Now I have a clear understanding of the codebase. The key function is `loadTaskFile` in `src/lib/task-store.ts` (line 168-189). Currently, it has a bare `catch` that silently returns `null` when YAML parsing fails. I need to wrap it with a user-friendly error message that includes the filename.\n\nLet me also look at `loadTasksFromStore` and `loadArchiveFromStore` to see how they call `loadTaskFile`.","time":{"start":1773433294552,"end":1773433294552}}}
