{"type":"text","timestamp":1773433373015,"sessionID":"ses_31723c2d1ffefQggw4LJSMu73r","part":{"id":"prt_ce8dda58e0012IGqqK4kMjSzDF","sessionID":"ses_31723c2d1ffefQggw4LJSMu73r","messageID":"msg_ce8dd9d10001CehPQNsDRphHjL","type":"text","text":"All done. Here's a summary of what was implemented:\n\n## Summary\n\n**Problem:** When a task YAML file in `.wombo-combo/tasks/` was corrupted, the raw YAML library error was silently swallowed (bare `catch` blocks returning `null` or defaults), giving users no indication of what went wrong.\n\n**Fix:** Updated three bare `catch` blocks in `src/lib/task-store.ts` to emit user-friendly error messages:\n\n1. **`loadTaskFile()`** (line 188) — Now logs `\"Failed to parse <filename>.yml: <reason>\"` when a task file has invalid YAML\n2. **`loadMeta()`** (line 126) — Now logs `\"Failed to parse _meta.yml: <reason>\"` when the meta file has invalid YAML  \n3. **`migrateArchiveIfNeeded()`** (line 631) — Now logs `\"Failed to parse archive.yml: <reason>\"` when the legacy archive file has invalid YAML\n\nEach catch block extracts the error reason with `err instanceof Error ? err.message : String(err)` and outputs it via `console.error()` with the filename from `basename()`. The functions still return their graceful-degradation values (`null`, `defaultMeta()`, or `false`) to maintain the existing behavior of continuing operation despite corrupted files.\n\n- ✅ TypeScript typecheck passes\n- ✅ Build passes (0.93 MB bundle)\n- ✅ Committed as `fix(bug-yaml-parse-error)`","time":{"start":1773433373004,"end":1773433373004}}}
